No matter what, if you're addicted to drugs, alcohol, sex, gambling, food, online gaming or whatever<br>
<br>
Until you (meaning you personally) make a decision that you want to quit what you're doing, nothing will help you quit.  Its a tough decision to make, help support groups like AA and other similar 12 step programs are there for moral support, to let you know that you are not alone.<br>
<br>
When I quit drinking, I didn't go to A.A.  I've been in and out of the AA/NA program for 9 odd years before I quit drinking.  When I finally said &quot;I gotta change my life, I'm sick and tired of living like I was&quot; I just quit.<br>
<br>
Its a matter of choice, if you want to quit (insert addiction here)  you will just quit.  Until you're ready to quit nothing you or anyone else can say or do that will truly help you stop.<br>
<br>
